{
  "texts": [
    "However, employing a whole-body skeleton graph that encompasses all 136 nodes leads to reduced accuracy and augments the number of parameters in the model.",
    "We conduct a graph reduction on the whole-body skeleton graph and trim down the 136 nodes to 56 nodes.",
    "The remaining graph contains 21 nodes for each hand and 14 nodes for the upper body.",
    "For the RGB stream, we adopt S3D [12] networks, pre-trained on the Kinetics [11] and WLASL [6] datasets, due to their proven effectiveness in sign language recognition [16,18] and translation [18,31].",
    "Most importantly, compared to the I3D [11] model, S3D offers not only improved performance but also the advantage of being a lightweight model, which facilitates efficient deployment in real-time applications."
  ]
}